Hi folks,


We had a great turnout at our first meeting. Thanks to everyone who
attended. The notes are below:


*Hayes Court United*

*4/21/20 - Meeting Summary*

Video Call

# of Attendees: 13


Outreach Results

   -

   On Friday, April 17, we knocked on every door.
   -

   There are 56 units in total
   -

   37 units are in contact with us
   -

   25 of those units told us their concerns or answered our survey
   -

   19 units are not in contact with us


First Action: 311 Mass Request for an On-Site Super (We need you for this!)

   -

   WHEN: This weekend, Saturday April 25 & Sunday April 26
   -

   WHAT: All tenants who want to participate will call 311, text 311, or
   use the 311 website to report that we have not had an on-site super sinc=
e
   March 1st. An instructional flyer will be given to each apartment by Fri=
day.
   -

   WHY? By law, a super must be on-site or living within 200 feet or 1
   block, whichever is greater, for a building our size. The super=E2=80=99=
s contact
   info (name, address, phone number) must be posted publicly by law. They
   only provided us with management=E2=80=99s contact info. So we are doing=
 this
   action to create a record that the City has been informed of this violat=
ion.


Second Action: Repair Complaint Forms & Written Letter to Management (We
need you for this too!)

   -

   WHEN: May 1 through May 8, subject to change if needed.
   -

   By May 1, all units will receive a paper copy of the repair complaint
   form
   <https://www.metcouncilonhousing.org/wp-content/uploads/2011/02/Repair-C=
omplaint-Form.pdf>.
   We will hand-deliver or slip under doors. Please fill it out.
   -

   By May 8, we will collect the forms and send it to management. We will
   make copies and use certified mail to send the packet of complaints to
   management.
   -

   We will also draft a letter to management, have it reviewed and signed
   by tenants, and attach to the complaint forms.
   -

   WHY? To create a record that management has been informed of our repair
   and maintenance needs.


First Survey <https://forms.gle/6bYwwahct3toaKco6> Question Results: =E2=80=
=9CWhat
are your biggest concerns as a tenant?=E2=80=9D (25 responses)

